    "Benchmarking of optimization algorithmsWith an increasing number of optimization algorithms, an effort to benchmark their performance is required.",
    "Felton et al. [76] have highlighted the fact that the ability of an algorithm to perform well in a specific task may not translate universally to other problems, and thus a specific algorithm for chemical reaction optimization may have different performances depending on the nature of the target variables, objectives, and chemical reaction.",
